    • Method Detail

      • getLogicalStartTime

        long getLogicalStartTime()
        Returns the logical start time of the Batch Job. Logical start time is the time when this Batch job is supposed to start if this job is started by the scheduler. Otherwise it would be the current time when the job runs.
        Returns:
        Time in milliseconds since epoch time (00:00:00 January 1, 1970 UTC).

        V - value type
        Parameters:
        datasetName - name of the Dataset
        arguments - arguments for the Dataset
        splits - list of Split or null to use the default splits provided by the Dataset
        Returns:
        A new JavaPairRDD instance that reads from the given Dataset
        Throws:
        DatasetInstantiationException - if the Dataset doesn't exist

      • fromStream

        <V> org.apache.spark.api.java.JavaPairRDD<Long,V> fromStream(String streamName,
                                                           Class<V> valueType)
        Creates a JavaPairRDD that represents all events from the given stream. The key in the resulting JavaPairRDD is the event timestamp. The stream body will be decoded as the give value type. Currently it supports Text, String and ByteWritable.
        Parameters:
        streamName - name of the stream
        valueType - type of the stream body to decode to
        Returns:
        A new JavaRDD instance that reads from the given stream
        Throws:
        DatasetInstantiationException - if the Stream doesn't exist

      • fromStream

        <V> org.apache.spark.api.java.JavaPairRDD<Long,V> fromStream(String streamName,
                                                           long startTime,
                                                           long endTime,
                                                           Class<V> valueType)
        Creates a JavaPairRDD that represents events from the given stream in the given time range. The key in the resulting JavaPairRDD is the event timestamp. The stream body will be decoded as the give value type. Currently it supports Text, String and ByteWritable.
        Parameters:
        streamName - name of the stream
        startTime - the starting time of the stream to be read in milliseconds (inclusive)
        endTime - the ending time of the streams to be read in milliseconds (exclusive)
        valueType - type of the stream body to decode to
        Returns:
        A new JavaRDD instance that reads from the given stream
        Throws:
        DatasetInstantiationException - if the Stream doesn't exist

      • fromStream

        <K,V> org.apache.spark.api.java.JavaPairRDD<K,V> fromStream(String streamName,
                                                          long startTime,
                                                          long endTime,
                                                          Class<? extends StreamEventDecoder<K,V>> decoderClass,
                                                          Class<K> keyType,
                                                          Class<V> valueType)
        Creates a JavaPairRDD that represents events from the given stream in the given time range. Each steam event will be decoded by an instance of the given StreamEventDecoder class.
        Parameters:
        streamName - name of the stream
        startTime - the starting time of the stream to be read in milliseconds (inclusive)
        endTime - the ending time of the streams to be read in milliseconds (exclusive)
        decoderClass - the StreamEventDecoder for decoding StreamEvent
        keyType - the type of the decoded key
        valueType - the type of the decoded value
        Returns:
        A new JavaRDD instance that reads from the given stream
        Throws:
        DatasetInstantiationException - if the Stream doesn't exist
